---

The Ju Solfège Chromatic System (the musical theory itself, as distinct from this
software implementation) was conceived and developed by Paisan Chamnong
(JiewJumnong) as an original contribution to music education and singing
voice synthesis. The system's naming convention — using the 'i' vowel for
chromatic sharps and the 'u' vowel for chromatic flats — is the intellectual
property of its inventor.
